</table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uiamwotan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>I am Wotan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.thegamevine.com/~Wotan_Rogue/yinyang.gif border=0 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/23/01 9:30:35 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.thegamevine.com/~Wotan_Rogue/mask2a.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Charming and Pickpocket on new PVP Server?</span><hr size=1> I think they should both go back in.  Only to opposing teams of course.  <br>
<br>
The exploiting issues are moot, on a server where xp loss is a legitimate byproduct of PvP.  Charm can be used to make your corpse hard to recover, but I don't think there is anyplace where its impossible?<br>
<br>
Sure would add a bit of fun value.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><font size=5 color="gray"><b>Wotan</b><font size=3> Shaman Elder of the <a href="http://www.talonguard.org/shanks"><font color="red">Shanks</font></a> <br>

<font size=2><b><i>It is better to have less thunder in the mouth and more lightning in the hand.  - Apache Proverb</font></font></font></i></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukambic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kambic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/23/01 9:38:59 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.theglobe.com/Kambic/TRINITY.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Charming and Pickpocket on new PVP Server?</span><hr size=1> Yeah, with training, exp-killing, and the like acceptable, even encouraged, I think that charm/fear ought to go back in, because those were the reasons it was taken out.<br>
<br>
As for pick pocket, I think it should go in as +/-5 levels, and it makes the chinkling sound like when you buy/sell somthing (the victim hears it, or maybe only if unsuccesful).<br>
<br>
<br>
